      "versionNonce": 787583543,
      "isDeleted": false,
      "boundElements": null,
      "updated": 1773284164787,
      "link": null,
      "locked": false,
      "text": "So, basically It saves on ACTIVATIONS and COMPUTE:\n\n→ FP16 matrix multiplications are 2× faster on modern GPUs (Tensor Cores)\n\n→ Activation memory during forward pass is halved\n\n→ This is where the real speedup comes from — not parameter memory",
      "fontSize": 36,
      "fontFamily": 5,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "containerId": "MRrIJMtI16lnhf2ueBc-P",
      "originalText": "So, basically It saves on ACTIVATIONS and COMPUTE:\n\n→ FP16 matrix multiplications are 2× faster on modern GPUs (Tensor Cores)\n\n→ Activation memory during forward pass is halved\n\n→ This is where the real speedup comes from — not parameter memory",
      "autoResize": true,
      "lineHeight": 1.25
    },
